Thin channel inlet with time-varying Umean
==========================================

Demonstrates the syntheticTurbulenceInlet on a channel cross-section
(walls on two opposing sides, periodic on the others) with a
time-varying mean speed driven by a Function1 table.

Geometry            Channel (geometryMode = channel, walls on long edge).
Inlet target        Umean read from the table file
                    RandomForcing_InletU.dat via Function1<scalar>.
Friction velocity   Auto-computed from the bulk Reynolds number.
Solver              foamRun, incompressibleFluid.

Run with:           ./Allrun
Clean with:         ./Allclean

Notes
-----
The table file in this directory provides a time series of bulk speeds
that are then used as the area-averaged target Umean each timestep.
Replace the table with your own forcing trace (any Function1 type:
constant, table, polynomial, sine, coded, ...) to drive different inlet
forcing patterns.
